description: Check out this Absolutely Show Quality 1970 Buick Skylark with only 32000 actual miles. This car was sold new in the same town in Iowa that I purchased it in. It has been very well kept over the years by the previous two owners until it was cosmetically and mechanically restored about 4 years ago. Its dark green paint was repainted to a show quality shine on a super straight and solid original body. Its door jambs still support all of its original dark green paint. Its floors frame and trunk are all rock solid and detailed with brand new dual exhaust. It is powered by its #'s matching 350 engine that has had a 4bb intake carburetor and a nice lopey cam installed a few years ago during its restoration. It comes equipped with its original automatic transmission power steering hood tachometer dual exhaust fresh chrome on the original bumpers working Sonoma tic am radio and is riding on a great looking rally rims with BFG RWL tires. Its original green bench seat interior is in perfect condition with an exception of one small crack on its original dash pad. This car might have started life as a plain skylark but with its GS emblems GS hood hood Tachometer and its correct ram air induction all in place this is defiantly a Gran Sport now. Come and check this car out you will not be disappointed. Want a nice muscle car you can show and drive with confidence this is it! Please watch our 8 minute video on our home website www.coyoteclassics.com there you will see and hear this Skylark while driving down the road. I will also give you a full walk around description of its condition while the car is idling so you can hear it run.
